tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Finished T4 at the Mainland China Qualifying Tournament in early March at Wolong Lake GC in Liuzhou. Looked like he had shot himself out of a fully-exempt slot with a third-round 80 but recovered nicely with a 2-under 70 to secure his playing privileges for the season…In his 13th career Series' start, earned his first top-10 when he T10 at the Cadillac Championship in Beijing. Was par or better in all four rounds at Topwin G&CC—including a 5-under 67 Saturday—to tie with Xinjun Zhang, Daniel Pearce and Sejun Yoon.

2014: In seven PGA TOUR China Series events made four cuts—with a best finish a T23 at the United Investment Real Estate Wuhan Open.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the PGA Tour China Serie was T10th in 2015 at the Cadillac Championship.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks T60th in Scoring Average (Actual) on the PGA Tour China Series.
